Author: Hang Qu <quhang@stanford.edu>

Application "open2d" and "open3d" are for viewing simulation result.
Application "water" is a water simulation example, without Nimbus.

Instructions for building applications:
Please first build the PhysBAM library in folder "physbam-lib".
Go into the corresponding directory of the application you want to build, e.g.,
> cd water.
Then type:
> mkdir -p Build/Release
> cd Build/Release
> ccmake ../..
Configure the cmake options.
Finally, you can run make in the 'Build/Release' folder:

